# mcp: producer / orchestrator governance grants.
#
# The `mcp` context_type is where most orchestration / producer work happens —
# Claude Code drives kaijutsu over MCP (cheap on the Anthropic subscription),
# while kaijutsu itself runs local / cheaper models to keep API spend down. That
# producer role iterates on the kernel's own CRDT-owned config-as-code, so it
# holds the rc + config governance caps *on top of* the broad loadout composed in
# by S10 (the shared `lib` binding: "*", facade:*, drive/fork/drift/transport/
# operator).
#
# These are deny-by-default and NOT implied by "*": a broad role must not be able
# to rewrite a privileged lifecycle script or swap which model runs by accident.
# Granting them here is the explicit, intentional opt-in for the producer voice.
kj binding allow "rc-write"      # kj rc edit/reset + file-tool writes under /etc/rc
kj binding allow "config-write"  # kj config set/reset over the /etc/config CRDT files
